Set Up Your Service Console for Swarming

Optimize the agent swarming experience with swarming page layouts, tabs, and related lists.

Create a custom Lightning Console App:

* Add Swarming objects to the console appâ€™s navigation items:
	+ Swarms
	+ Swarm Members
	+ Cases
	+ Reports
	+ Dashboards
	+ Omni Supervisor (required)
	+ Service Resources (required)
* Assign the Lightning console app to Swarming user profiles

Add Swarms and Swarm Members Related lists to Page Layouts:

* Configure page layouts for objects (e.g. Case)
* Add Swarms and Swarm Members related lists
* Save changes

Create a Swarming tab on record pages:

* From the object in Object Manager, select Lightning Record Pages
* Select the record page and click Edit
* Add a tab named "Swarming" with Swarm and Swarm Member related list components
* Save changes

Show a swarm members list or swarms list for a record:

* Add Related List - Single component to the Console page layout under the Swarming tab
* Select Swarm Members or Swarms as the Related List
title: Setting Up Service Cloud Swarming
